  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Climate Media Collaborative for Economic Justice and Community Rights</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Meanwhile, the Indonesia Hub proposes goals and approaches focused on:  &#x2022; Growing online public engagement through creative competitions (short films, writing, fellowships, etc.) and social media campaigns. As part of this, support the digitalization and reach of partner&apos;s campaigns, through best practices story telling. &#x2022; Collaboratively working with journalists and journalist associations to amplify campaigns and supporting new alternative media platforms and channels (such as campaigning through podcasts) to reach a more diverse audience &#x2013; especially women, as well as urban and rural youth &#x2013; and prevent echo chambers. &#x2022; Mainstreaming economic alternatives and climate action as well as a green economic recovery from COVID. Focus on emphasizing women - and community -driven solutions to the climate crisis, especially the role that women farmers must play.</narrative>
  </description>
